         <div type="edition" xml:lang="kaw-Latn" rendition="class:38769 maturity:83213">
            <p>
                <lb n="1"/><g type="circleMed"/> bhaṭāra kakīṅ abhaya brat· <abbr>dhā</abbr> <num value="11">11</num>
                <lb n="2"/>bratniṁ mās ya <abbr>su</abbr> <num value="1">1</num> <abbr>mā</abbr> <num value="15">15</num>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div type="apparatus">
           <!--apparatus encoded as per EGD §9.1, basic elements for apparatus below-->
               <listApp><!-- one <app> for each apparatus entry -->
                  <app loc="1">
                     <lem>mās ya</lem>
                     <note>Brandes (in <bibl><ptr target="bib:Groeneveldt1887_01"/></bibl>) suggests the emendation <foreign>māsnya</foreign>, but this seems both unnecessary and impossible (because <foreign>-nya</foreign> cannot be used with reference to a deity).</note>
                  </app>
               </listApp>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" resp="part:argr">
 	<p>The deity at Abhaya: weight 11 <foreign>dhāraṇa</foreign>s. The weight of the gold, it is 1 <foreign>suvarṇa</foreign>, 15 <foreign>māṣa</foreign>s.</p>
         </div>
